attributes.Long form description: The student begins by changing the joy controllers to the comfort grip, when he finishes the student waits for new instructions. The instructor tells that he need no change the comfort grip to the joycon strap after that the student placed back the joycons on the Nintendo Switch and stand it using the kickstand, then he exchanged de game cartridge and the SD card to finally turn on and off the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: We will now operate the Nintendo switch.
The first task is to change the controller from the handheld mode to the joy-con comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student slides out the joy-con controllers.

attributes.Transcription: You have to press the small button in the back and slide out the colored part.
And it's the colored parts that you have to place on the grip

attributes.Action sentence: The student mounts the joy-con controller on the comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: The next step is to change the controller from the joy-con comfort grip to two joy-cons.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student doesn't need the tablet to execute the instructions given.

attributes.Transcription: The joy-cons are on the left.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the comfort grip for two joy-con controllers.

attributes.Transcription: So you have to take out the controllers.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The joy-con strap needs to be upside down.

attributes.Transcription: And if you want to lock it with the white lock and press it.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The joy-con controller needs to be install on the other side of the joy-con strap.

attributes.Transcription: The next step is to change the controller from the two joy-cons to the handheld mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the joy-con controllers for the handheld mode.

attributes.Transcription: Pull it down to unlock it.
And the controller, the color one, will go on the screen.
Now please, make the Nintendo stand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student stands the Nintendo switch on the table.

attributes.Transcription: There is a kickstand on the back.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should not can not find the right place

attributes.Transcription: Now please, change the game card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the game card.

attributes.Transcription: The next step is to change the micro sd card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the sd card.

attributes.Transcription: Now please turn on the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo switch.
The student turns off the Nintendo switch.

attributes.Transcription: To turn it off, you have to press it for three seconds.
We will go to the power options, you can use the touch screen as well.
You can now stop the recording.
